SocketApplication.class/--preface--      SocketApplication.class/--preface--

        SocketApplication.class masters Socket.class and its derivatives. It
        is responsible for calling event notifies, namely ESM_Socket_Event#?
        methods.

SocketApplication.class/ESA_Application_Child

   NAME
        ESA_Application_Child -- (V1 ) [IS.], *Object

   FUNCTION
        Add new member.  When the socket app object gets disposed all members
        are disposed recursively.  This way DisposeObject(SocketApp) is
        enough to delete the entire object tree.

   NOTES
        Do NOT add objects from hostile systems or you are quickly visited
        by the great guru. Only add objects created from Socket.class or its
        derivatives!

   BUGS
        Take great care when removing individual objects from an object tree.

   SEE ALSO
        Socket.class/ESA_Socket_Child

