SocketApplication.class/ESM_Application_AddEventHandler

   NAME ESM_Application_AddEventHandler (V1 )

   SYNOPSIS
        DoMethod(obj,ESM_Application_AddEventHandler,struct ES_EventHandler ehnode);

   FUNCTION
        Sometimes it becomes useful wait for certain signals but since
        classes can't deal with the main loop event handlers are introduced.

        You must fill out a event handler node and call
        ESM_Application_AddEventHandler with the structure as parameter.
        From now on your object will receive the specified method whenever
        one of the given signals arrives.

        You can add and remove event handler nodes any time as long as you
        know your application object.

   INPUTS
        ehnode - Pointer to an initialized ES_EventHandler structure:
                signals - signals you wish to be notified on.
                object  - fill in a pointer to your object.
                method  - method that you want to receive.
                flags   - always set to 0 for now.

   NOTES
        You must match each AddEventHandler with exactly one
        RemoveEventHandler method.

   SEE ALSO
        ESM_Application_RemoveEventHandler

SocketApplication.class/ESM_Application_AllocMem

   NAME
        ESM_Application_AllocMem (V1 )

   SYNOPSIS
        memoryBlock = DoMethod(obj,ESM_Application_AllocMem,ULONG byteSize);

   FUNCTION
        Allocate memory from private pool.  Memory is freed *automatically*
        when the app object gets disposed.

   INPUTS
        byteSize - the size of the desired block in bytes.

   RESULT
        memoryBlock - a pointer to the newly allocated memory block or NULL.

   NOTE
        In the future memory allocated by this method may be swapped out if
        virtual memory is present in system. This is just private memory for
        your own use.

